       <p>
        <code>flex-direction</code> defines (surprisingly) the direction of the <b>main-axis</b>, defining the direction which flex items are placed in the flex container.
        <br>
        Flexbox is single-direction, which means the flex items can only lay out in a certain orientation (whether it is vertical or horizontal)
      </p>
      <p>
        <code>flex-direction</code> can asume four different values: 
      </p>

